│ THOUGHT: Now I need to understand the actual bug. The error message shows   │
│ that the insertelement instruction does not dominate its use. This is a     │
│ classic dominance issue. The vectorizer creates an insertelement in some    │
│ basic block, but the shufflevector that uses it is in a different block     │
│ where the insertelement doesn't dominate.                                   │
│                                                                             │
│ Looking at the test case, the function has multiple basic blocks with PHI   │
│ nodes. The vectorizer is trying to vectorize across basic blocks. The       │
│ sitofp instructions are in different blocks, but they all use the same      │
│ argument %0. The vectorizer creates a vectorized version of %0 (broadcast)  │
│ but places it in the wrong block.                                           │
│                                                                             │
│ The fix should be to ensure that when creating a vectorized value for a     │
│ scalar that is used in multiple blocks, we place it in a block that         │
│ dominates all uses. The nearest common dominator of all uses would be       │
│ appropriate.                                                                │
